<tip category="Raki|app">
<html>
<p>RAKI lets you easily install Windows CE software on your device. 
<ul>
<li>Simply drag a cab-file from Konqueror and drop it onto the RAKI icon in 
the System-Tray or</li>
<li>Right-click
on a cab-file in Konqueror and select <em>Install CAB-File</em> from the context
menu.
</li>
</ul>
</p>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="Raki|app">
<html>
<p>If you choose to use VDCCM instead of DCCM raki lets you control more
than one devices at the same time.</p>
<p>Left-click on the RAKI icon pops up the <b>Connected Devices</b> menu where every connected
device is represented with its own device-menu item.</p>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="Raki|app">
<html>
<p>Every connected device could be configured individualy. Try the <b>Configure</b>
menu item in an arbitrary device-menu.<p>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="Raki|app">
<html>
<p>Select synchronization types desired to be synchronized individualy for every device in the
device specific configration menu.</p>
</html>
</tip>
<tip category="Raki|app">
<html>
<p>Select synchronization types desired to be synchronized individualy for every device in the
device specific configration menu.
</p>
</html>
</tip>

